            "id": "4451491",
            "title": "Assicurazioni Generali S.p.A. reports Q1 results",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Assicurazioni Generali S.p.A. <a href=\"https://www.generali.com/doc/jcr:a4d02d83-1725-4eeb-a550-d0c5f0b99748/05.22%20PR%20Generali%20Financial%20Information%20as%20of%2031%20March%202025_def.pdf/lang:en/05.22_PR_Generali_Financial_Information_as_of_31_March_2025_def.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">press release</a>  (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ARZGF\" title=\"Assicurazioni Generali S.p.A.\">OTCPK:ARZGF</a>):</li>\n<li>Adjusted EPS rose even more strongly to € 0.79 (+9.4%)</li>\n<li>Q1 Gross written premiums reached € 26.5 billion (+0.2%), driven by the strong performance of P&amp;C (+8.6%), especially in Non-Motor</li>\n<li>Life net inflows exceeded € 3.0 billion thanks to all business lines, particularly Protection &amp; Health</li>\n<li>Combined Ratio improved substantially to 89.7% (-1.4 p.p.). The undiscounted Combined Ratio also continued its very positive development to 92.0% (-1.7 p.p.)</li>\n<li>Operating result grew significantly to € 2.1 billion (+8.9%), thanks to the contribution from all business segments, led by strong P&amp;C performance</li>\n<li>Adjusted net result increased to € 1.2 billion (+7.6%).</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
